<h1><span id="Pirc_Defence">Pirc Defence</span></h1>
<h3><span id="1...d6">1...d6</span></h3>
<p>In this opening, Black does not immediately fight for the center, but prefers to prepare counter-play while White advances White's pawns.
</p><p>If White dislikes this opening, White can play 2. Nf3 in order to transpose into the Sicilian Defence (2...c5) or into the Philidor Defence (2...e5).
</p><p>If White agrees to play this defence, White has no reason not to build its pawn center with 2. d4.
</p>
<p><b>1. e4 d6</b>
